The paper is about recommender systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a neural network-based model for collaborative filtering, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The model utilizes a heterogeneous information network, which is a type of network analysis (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of auxiliary information, which is a common topic in social network analysis (cs.SOC). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on real-world datasets, which is a common practice in database research (cs.DB).
